<!doctype html>
<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-T002 Project Packet</title><style>@page{margin:.6in}body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;line-height:1.45;color:#111827;max-width:8.1in;margin:0 auto;background:#fff}h1{background:#1f2937;color:#fff;padding:16px 18px;border-radius:10px;font-size:22pt;margin:0 0 14px}h2{color:#0f172a;border-bottom:2px solid #cbd5e1;padding-bottom:4px;margin:18px 0 8px;font-size:15pt}p{margin:8px 0 12px}ul{margin:8px 0 14px 24px}li{margin:4px 0}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;table-layout:fixed;margin:10px 0 16px}th,td{border:1px solid #b7c3d0;padding:8px 9px;vertical-align:top;word-wrap:break-word}th{background:#dbeafe;color:#0f172a;text-align:left}.meta{background:#f8fafc;border:1px solid #dbe3ec;border-radius:10px;padding:10px 12px}.visual{text-align:center;margin:12px 0 16px}.visual img{width:100%;max-width:7.15in;height:auto;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;border-radius:10px}.phase{background:#eff6ff;border-left:6px solid #0ea5e9;padding:10px 12px;margin:10px 0;border-radius:6px}.small{font-size:9pt;color:#475569;border-top:1px solid #e2e8f0;padding-top:8px;margin-top:18px}</style></head>
<body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - Project Packet</h1><p class="meta"><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T002<br><b>Package:</b> Project Packet<br><b>Scenario:</b> 28x40 garage idea to layout and build order</p><div class="visual"><img src="../assets/sample-garage-proof.svg" alt="Garage project visual"></div><h2>Customer input received</h2><ul><li>Outside dimension: 28 ft x 40 ft.</li><li>Two overhead doors on short side with space between doors and about 2 ft to corners.</li><li>Uses: vehicle parking, workbench, tool storage, seasonal storage, small project work.</li><li>Customer wants a practical order before buying storage or cabinets.</li></ul><h2>Zone plan</h2><table><colgroup><col style="width:22%"><col style="width:28%"><col style="width:25%"><col style="width:25%"></colgroup><tr><th>Zone</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Placement rule</th><th>Do first</th></tr><tr><td>Vehicle lane</td><td>Keep one vehicle bay usable.</td><td>Starts at overhead door and stays clear.</td><td>Mark clear lane before moving storage.</td></tr><tr><td>Workbench zone</td><td>Repair, assembly, layout, small jobs.</td><td>Near power and daily tools.</td><td>Measure outlet locations and walking clearance.</td></tr><tr><td>Wall storage</td><td>Seasonal storage, parts, bins, long items.</td><td>Keep off floor where possible.</td><td>Choose wall rail or shelving after dimensions.</td></tr><tr><td>Dirty work zone</td><td>Grinding, cutting, messy repair.</td><td>Away from clean storage and parked vehicle.</td><td>Mark safe distance and ventilation concern.</td></tr></table><h2>Build order</h2><div class="phase"><b>Phase 1 - Confirm:</b> measure wall lengths, ceiling height, overhead door tracks, outlets, lights, and heater clearance.</div><div class="phase"><b>Phase 2 - Clear:</b> create vehicle lane, temporary sort zone, trash pile, keep pile, and unknown pile.</div><div class="phase"><b>Phase 3 - Install:</b> wall rail/shelving, daily tool zone, parts staging shelf, labels.</div><div class="phase"><b>Phase 4 - Upgrade later:</b> lighting, heat, cabinets, compressed air, better workbench, dust/dirty work separation.</div><h2>Material groups</h2><table><colgroup><col style="width:30%"><col style="width:45%"><col style="width:25%"></colgroup><tr><th>Group</th><th>Examples</th><th>Buy now?</th></tr><tr><td>Measurement/layout</td><td>Tape, painter tape, marker, graph paper, labels.</td><td>Yes</td></tr><tr><td>Storage</td><td>Wall rails, hooks, shelving, labeled totes.</td><td>After measurements</td></tr><tr><td>Workbench</td><td>Bench top, legs/base, power strip, task light.</td><td>After parking lane is confirmed</td></tr><tr><td>Later upgrades</td><td>Cabinets, lighting, heater, air lines.</td><td>No, not first spend</td></tr></table><h2>Customer-ready summary</h2><p>Your garage problem is not a full remodel yet. The correct first win is to protect a vehicle lane, assign storage zones, and delay expensive cabinets until the wall and ceiling measurements are confirmed.</p><p class="small">Highway 38 Solutions - Big problems. Clear plans. Hypothetical sample deliverable.</p></body></html>